 <br>
  A lot of people say innate camo, but it's just a small convience.  Almost exactly never do you need to invis that fast or for that long that Imp Sup Camo won't do the job.  It's too bad it isn't 1 or 2 points.<br>
 <br>
  MGB... um... even if your guild has marzin it's still an utter and complete waste of points.  You get a whole 45 extra HPs over group Aego at a cost of an extra buff slot and 36AC.  If it's that important to you it's much easier to simply cabbage a couple wizards and the MTs that want the 45 extra HPs.  If everyone insists on it a pair of druids can easily glades 8 groups in under a minute, we have no other buffs we're really blowing mana on, and with a zillion clerics at a raid if they bitch about marzining a couple people they can shove it.  MGB is just utterly and totally pointless for druids.  Let the shamans get it.<br>
 <br>
  Dire charm is so rarely useful for druids theres really no point.  Spending 9 points on this pile of crap is pitiful.  For soloing you're always better off using Call of Karana, breaking charm and getting 2 full xp kills.  For groups it's only useful in Chardok.  The BEST use for dire charm?  Getting faction while you sleep.  Park the pet at a spawn it can solo and go to a safe spot in the zone and go to sleep, gain a few faction points overnight.<br>
 <br>
  Quick damage isn't actually all that good, but compared to the rest of the junk druids get it's among the best.  Letting you get nukes off on those unsnarable mobs faster or make less channeling failures when you're tank/nuking something.  Saddly it's obscenely expensive.<br>
 <br>
  Exodus is nice, unfortunatly it will leave you behind occasionally which might make you want to firebomb VI after ripping their gonads off and shoving them down their throats.  Or maybe thats just me.  I've had it interrupted lots, and I've also been able to get it to go while running.  It doesn't work in PoF last I checked though, much to my surprise and misfortune when I was checking a spawn... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulysianderschattenwald.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lysiander Schattenwald</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#333399>(6/3/02 4:20:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27482.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.htp-tel.de/vhennings/sig/Elf1L.jpg height=170 width=110></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What is the best aa in c l a s s area to train in?</span><hr size=1> The Point in using Marzins and PotG instead of Aego is the nice 6 Mana regen per tick you would otherwise not have. This mana regen has saved countless guildmembers of mine on Raids because i had the mana to heal when all other druids where OOM.<br>
